-1 CREATION~
The creation spell group is used to create objects, of temporary or permanent
duration.  Skill creators can travel without food or drink, and use their 
powers to create nourishment as required.  All classes may become learned in
this group, which contains these spells:

continual light	creates an eternal light source
create food	produces a nourishing mushroom
create rose	creates a beautiful red rose
create spring	calls forth a small but pure spring from the ground
create water	fills any available container with water
floating disc	creates a floating disc of force perfect for hauling treasure
~

-1 WEATHER~
These spells allow the caster to manipulate local weather conditions, as well
as summon fog clouds, lightning, or even electrical glows.  This group is
usable by all classes.

call lightning	summons a huge bolt from the heavens, if the weather is right
control weather	changes the weather in the manner desired by the caster
faerie fire	surrounds the target in a glowing aura
faerie fog	reveals all hidden creatures in the room
lightning bolt	sends a bolt of electricity into the target

(the weather command, unrelated to this group, shows local weather conditions)
~

0 MINE GEMMINE~
Skill Type: Active
Command: mine/gemmine

The mine and gemmine skills are used to gather raw materials that can be
used to craft armor and jewelry with the appropriate skills.  This can only
be done in rooms where mining and gemmining are allowed, which are
designated by having a '$$$$$$' sign in the room description.  Mountainous
areas will provide silver/rubies, areas near water will provide
copper/diamonds, and desert areas will provide gold and iron/emeralds.
Training these skills increases the likelyhood of receiving better quality
ores and gems, up to a quality of 'perfect'.
 
It costs {Y50 gold{x to mine/gemmine.
~

0 HUNT~
Skill Type: Active
Command: hunt <target>

The hunt skill is used to track down targets in the area you're in,
giving a sense of the direction you need to go in order to find your target.
Training this skill makes it more likely that your direction sense will be
accurate.  

The hunt skill can only be used if you are in the same area; you cannot be
in Illian and attempt to hunt someone that is in Tear.  In addition, there
must be a path that can be followed between your current location and your
target.  Certain mobs are trained in stealth and hiding their trail and
cannot be located with this skill.  
~

-1 BERSERK~
Only powerful characters can master berserking, the ability to enter
insane rage in combat.  Its effects are not altogether unlike the frenzy
spell -- a huge surge of combat prowess, coupled with a disregard for
personal safety.  Berserking characters are more resistant to the effects of
weaves.  
~

-1 DIRT 'DIRT KICKING'~
Consider by some to be a cowardly skill, dirt kicking gives the clever 
combatant a chance to blind his opponent by casting dirt into his eyes.  The
blindness does not last long, but can provide an edge in combat.  Dexterity
helps in hitting or avoiding a dirt kick.  Only warriors and thieves may
learn this skill.
~

0 PUSH~
Skill Type: Active
Command: push/drag <target> <direction>

The push skill allows you to move players and mobs out of the room
they're in, either to get them out of the way or to group them together for
some purpose.  Training this skill makes it more likely to work.  

You increase your chances of pushing someone by having a higher level,
higher strength or larger size than them.  Some mobs cannot be pushed at
all, and others who are strong enough to resist your attempts may try to
push you instead.  Any exit you try to push someone through must be open, so
you cannot push someone through a locked door.  Keep in mind that some targets
may not appreciate being pushed and can attack you, so be careful!

The push skill only works on targets that are standing; for those that are
sitting or sleeping, use the drag command instead.  
~

0 ARMORCRAFT JEWELCRAFT~
Skill Type: Active
Command: armorcraft/jewelcraft <wear slot> <first ore> <second ore/first gem>

The armorcraft and jewelcraft skills are used to create pieces or armor
or jewelry out of the ores and gems gathered by the mine and gemmine skills.
Armor can be created for the legs, hands, arms, body or head, and requires
two ore of at least flawless quality.  Jewelry can be created for the neck,
ears or finger and requires one ore and one gem of at least flawless
quality.  In both cases, higher-quality ores and gems will make stronger
pieces of equipment.  Training these skills makes creating armor and jewelry
successfully more likely.  
 
It costs {Y150 gold{x to armorcraft/jewelcraft.
~

