0 ENVENOM~
Skill Type: Active
Command: envenom <weapon>/<food object>

The envenom skill allows thieves to apply poison either to their weapons
or a food item in order to give them an edge in combat.  Envenomed weapons
have a chance to poison your target, which saps their strength and deals a
small amount of damage.  Envenoming food has the same chance, but obviously
requires the target to eat the item in question.  The chaos of combat will
quickly remove venom from weapons.  Training this skill makes it more likely
to work.  

One thing to note: If this skill is used ICly to poison targets (either
through combat or with food), both characters must agree beforehand
regarding the severity of the poison.  If someone attempts to use poisoned
food ICly and then claim that someone is dead without a chance at healing
when they eat it, there will be SEVERE consequences.  
~

-1 'HAND TO HAND'~
Hand to hand combat is a rare skill in the lands of the Wheel of Time. 
Learning this style of fighting gives the player a weapon even when disarmed
-- bare hands.  Trained hand to hand experts are far more effective than
many swordsmen.  Warriors are the best at this skill, although thieves and
channelers may also learn it.  
~

0 KICK~
Skill Type: Active, Attacking
Command: kick <target>
Initiates Combat: Yes
Used In Combat: Yes

The kick command is used to deal damage to your target.  It deals a small
amount of damage, but can be done twice a round, and can also be used to
force mobs or players to attack you.  Training this skill increases the
likelihood of the kick working and the damage you deal with it.  
~

0 WEAPONSMITH~
Skill Type: Active
Command: weaponsmith axe/dagger/mace/spear/sword iron <second ore>

The weaponsmith skill allows weapons to be forged and used by the player.
It requires two iron ore and an additional ore (gathered by the mining
skill), all of the same quality; better-quality ores mean a stronger weapon.
The additional ore used will help in determining the additional stats of the
weapon (hitroll, damroll, hp/end, etc.)  The skill can be used to make
swords, axes, maces, spears and daggers.  Training the skill makes creating
the weapons successfully more likely.  

It costs {Y150 gold{x to weaponsmith.  
~

0 RESCUE~
Skill Type: Active
Command: rescue <grouped player>

The rescue skill allows you to remove someone who is in your group from
combat and gain the focus of their opponent in their place.  The target will
no longer be in combat (though they can still be attacked again!)  And you
will instead be fighting the opponent that was fighting them.  The
possibility of this skill working is based on your skill level as well as
your dexterity and level compared to the person you're rescuing.  
~

0 TRIP BASH~
Skill Type: Active, Attacking
Command: trip/bash <target>
Initiates Combat: Yes
Used In Combat: Yes

The trip and bash skills both allow you to force a target you are
fighting to the ground, though in different ways.  Targets that are tripped
or bashed will find themselves dazed, which makes them unable to attack and
makes many other combat skills more difficult or impossible to do.  Training
these skills makes them more likely to work.  

In both cases, being larger than your opponent will assist you both with
tripping/bashing them and resisting their trip/bash attempts, and people
with good reflexes have an easier time avoiding trip/bash attempts as well. 
People or mobs affected by the levitate weave cannot be tripped, but cannot
trip others in response, and those affected by the wrap weave cannot trip or
bash.  Those with good concentration find it easier to act if they are
tripped/bashed.  
~

0 'CRITICAL STRIKE'~
Skill Type: Passive

The critical strike skill gives you a chance to perform an attack for
more damage with weapons and fists (not weaves).  Critical strikes from
standard attacks will display '*C*' beside them.  Some active combat skills
can also benefit from the critical strike skill as well.  Training this
skill increases the likelihood of gaining critical strikes.  

Keep in mind that mobs also have access to the critical strike skill, and
they can and will use it on you!  
~

0 'ARMOR USE'~
Skill Type: Passive

The armor use skill reduces the amount of damage taken from attacks by
weapons and fists (not weaves).  Training this skill reduces damage further.
~

0 HIDE SNEAK~
Skill Type: Active
Command: hide/sneak

The hide and sneak skills are both related to being undetected.  Hiding
gives you a chance to be not seen in a room by others as long as you don't
move, and sneaking gives you a chance to move from room to room without
others seeing you enter/leave.  Training these skills makes it more likely
that you will be able to successfully hide/sneak and makes it less likely
you will be noticed; these skills are opposed by the awareness skill (hide)
and the alertness skill (sneak).  

There are other, smaller benefits to hiding and sneaking; some attacks that
are best started from the shadows are more likely to succeed while hiding,
and aggressive mobs may not notice you sneaking around if you keep moving.  
 
To stop hiding/sneaking, use the 'vis' command.
~

